cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.FL, cs.THEORY. 

The paper deals with a variant of Dybvig et al.'s calculus of multi-prompted delimited-control operators with dynamic prompt generation, which is a programming language concept. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper also presents reasoning principles that generalize and advance existing techniques for establishing program equivalence, which suggests categories such as cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also discusses up-to techniques facilitating bisimulation proofs, which could fall under cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) or cs.THEORY (Theoretical Computer Science).
